The bundled certificate data in `cacert.pem` is extracted from
Mozilla's NSS root certificate store and is licensed under the
Mozilla Public License, version 2.0.

The full license text is available at:

    https://www.mozilla.org/MPL/2.0/

Source bundle (extracted by the curl project):

    https://curl.se/docs/caextract.html
    https://curl.se/ca/cacert.pem

The extraction tool (`mk-ca-bundle.pl`) is part of the curl project
and is licensed under curl's MIT/X derivative license; it generates
`cacert.pem` from Mozilla's `certdata.txt`.  Only the generated PEM
file is redistributed here, not the extraction tool itself.
